body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, this is Jeffrey Sanchez from ABC Auto Group. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Kathleen. Could you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is seven eight one - two three four - five six seven eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Kathleen. Next, could you share with me your email address?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email is kathleen.price@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Kathleen. Is there anything specific you would like to know about our inventory?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling nervous about choosing the right car. Can you help me with that?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Certainly, Kathleen. I'm here to assist you every step of the way. Thank you for reaching out and sharing your concerns. Your peace of mind is important to us.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Kathleen. If you have any more questions, feel free to contact me. Have a great day!
